                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/2043: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-29T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 29, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 29—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>764. 1. A German decree of December 14 published in <hi rend="italic"
                        >Reichsgesetzblatt</hi> 1 of December 23 received this morning provides
                    (insofar as we are able to interpret it) for the elimination of Jews as managers
                        (<hi rend="italic">Betriebs Führer</hi>) of plants or as acting
                    managers.</p>
                <p>2. I am sending a third-person note under today’s date to the Foreign Office
                    requesting assurances that American citizens will be exempted from its
                    application.</p>
                <p>3. I wish to add that I felt it desirable to take this position. We are, however,
                    unable to ascertain as yet whether as a practical issue American citizens are
                    actually affected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
